<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-40-0096 </DOCNO><TEXT>The traditional Australian coal miner is extremely conservative and doubtfulof the value of electronics. This conservative view is gradually beingovercome as the more progressive and innovative mines demonstrate theworth of electronics in reducing cost and increasing efficiency. Thepenetration of electronics into the mines is coming from two major areas:the incorporation of modern componentry and intelligent sub-systems intomobile machinery and the spread of mine-wide monitoring and control systemsfor reasons of efficiency.</TEXT></DOC>